## 1. Creating Arrays

```python
import numpy as np

# --- From Python lists ---
a1 = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])                       # 1D array
a2 = np.array([[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]])                 # 2D array (matrix)
a3 = np.array([[[1,2],[3,4]],[[5,6],[7,8]]])          # 3D array (tensor)

# --- Built-in constructors ---
zeros   = np.zeros((3, 4))            # 3×4 matrix of 0.0
ones    = np.ones((2, 3, 4))          # 3D tensor of 1.0
full    = np.full((3, 3), 7)          # 3×3 filled with 7
eye     = np.eye(4)                   # 4×4 identity matrix (ML: initialisation)
empty   = np.empty((2, 2))            # Uninitialised memory — fastest, unread values

# --- Range-based ---
arange  = np.arange(0, 10, 2)        # [0, 2, 4, 6, 8]  — like Python range()
linspace= np.linspace(0, 1, 5)       # [0.0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0] — evenly spaced

# --- Specifying dtype ---
int_arr = np.array([1.9, 2.7, 3.2], dtype=np.int32)   # [1, 2, 3] — truncated
f16_arr = np.array([1, 2, 3],       dtype=np.float16)  # half-precision (saves GPU RAM)
bool_arr= np.array([1, 0, 1, 1, 0], dtype=bool)        # [True False True True False]
```

