## 2. Array Attributes

```python
arr = np.array([[1, 2, 3],
                [4, 5, 6]])

print(arr.shape)     # (2, 3)       — (rows, columns)
print(arr.ndim)      # 2            — number of dimensions
print(arr.size)      # 6            — total elements
print(arr.dtype)     # int64        — data type
print(arr.nbytes)    # 48           — memory in bytes (6 × 8 bytes for int64)
print(arr.itemsize)  # 8            — bytes per element
```

> 💡 In ML: `arr.shape` is the most-used attribute.
> `(batch_size, seq_len, hidden_dim)` — understanding shape is understanding the model.

