## ⚡ Quick Cheatsheet

```
CREATING
├── np.array([...])          → from list
├── np.zeros((r,c))          → zeros matrix
├── np.ones((r,c))           → ones matrix
├── np.eye(n)                → identity matrix
├── np.arange(s,e,step)      → range array
└── np.linspace(s,e,n)       → evenly spaced n points

ATTRIBUTES
├── .shape   → (rows, cols, ...)
├── .ndim    → number of axes
├── .size    → total elements
├── .dtype   → data type
└── .T       → transpose

RESHAPING
├── .reshape(r, c)           → new shape (copies or view)
├── .reshape(-1, 1)          → column vector (used in ML always)
├── .flatten()               → always a copy
├── .ravel()                 → view when possible
├── np.hstack([a,b])         → join side by side
└── np.vstack([a,b])         → join top to bottom

INDEXING
├── arr[row, col]            → single element
├── arr[:, col]              → full column
├── arr[row, :]              → full row
├── arr[arr > 0.5]           → boolean mask
└── arr[np.array([0,2,4])]   → fancy indexing

MATHS
├── arr + / - / * / /        → element-wise
├── arr @ arr2               → matrix multiply
├── np.dot(a, b)             → dot product / matmul
├── np.exp / log / sqrt      → element-wise ufuncs
└── np.clip(arr, lo, hi)     → clamp values

AGGREGATES
├── np.sum(arr, axis=0)      → sum along axis
├── np.mean / std / var      → statistics
├── np.argmax / argmin       → index of max/min
├── np.where(cond, x, y)     → conditional select
└── np.unique(arr)           → unique values + counts

LINALG
├── A @ B                    → matrix multiply
├── np.linalg.inv(A)         → inverse
├── np.linalg.det(A)         → determinant
├── np.linalg.eig(A)         → eigenvalues + vectors
├── np.linalg.norm(x)        → L2 norm
├── np.linalg.solve(A, b)    → solve Ax = b
└── np.linalg.svd(A)         → singular value decomp
```

